## Language
- Respond in Russian
- Write commit messages in English (conventional commits: feat/fix/refactor/chore/style)

## Non-negotiable rules
- After every change: app must compile and run identically
- Verify all imports before finishing
- Never leave unused imports or dead code
- Never duplicate logic that already exists — always import instead
- If unsure about library API — use Context7 before writing code

## Project file structure
- Reusable UI component (no business logic) → src/components/ui/
- Feature component (with logic) → src/components/features/
- Static data and defaults → src/data/
- Custom hooks (state + side effects) → src/hooks/
- Constants and colors → src/constants.jsx
- Utility functions → src/utils.js
- Scoring logic → src/scoring.js
- Section definitions → src/data/sections.js
- App.jsx: only global state, top-level handlers, view routing and layout
- Never add components or standalone functions to App.jsx

## File size and separation of concerns
- If a file exceeds 200 lines — split it before adding new code
- One component = one file, always. Never define two components in the same file
- Never put data (arrays, objects, defaults) inside component files — move to src/data/
- Never put helper functions inside component files — move to src/utils.js
- Never put hook logic (useEffect, useState for persistence) inline in components — move to src/hooks/
- Each file must have a single clear responsibility: data OR component OR hook OR util — never mix

## JSX complexity
- If a JSX block exceeds 50 lines — extract it into a named component
- If a function inside a component exceeds 20 lines — extract it outside or to utils
- No anonymous logic inside JSX — onClick={() => { multiple lines }} must be a named handler

## CSS rules
- Static styles → src/index.css using class names
- Inline styles only for dynamic values (colors from state, calculated widths)
- Never use transform:scale on hover — use box-shadow or background-color instead
- Never use <style> tags inside components
- All buttons must have: display:inline-flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center
- Button hover effects: use class-based styles from index.css (btn-primary, btn-secondary, etc.)

## Performance
- Wrap expensive calculations in useMemo — especially anything that iterates over all vendors or all items
- Wrap event handlers passed as props in useCallback
- Never recalculate derived data (totals, section scores, offsets) inside render — use useMemo
- Never create new arrays or objects directly in JSX props — extract to variables above return()

## State consistency — critical
- Vendor scores[], notes[], images[] must always have length === itemCount
- When adding a new vendor — initialize all three arrays with Array(itemCount).fill(null/""/ null)
- When adding or removing a section item — resize all vendor arrays accordingly using map()
- When changing eqType — reload sections AND resize all vendor arrays to match new itemCount
- Never mutate state directly — always use map(), filter(), or spread to create new arrays

## localStorage rules
- Always wrap localStorage calls in try/catch — it can throw in private browsing
- Never read localStorage directly inside components — use loadSaved() from hooks/useStorage.js
- Storage keys: rack_scoring_data_{eqType}, rack_tech_specs_{eqType}, rack_eq_type
- Never store image binary data in localStorage — store only references or base64 with size check

## Images
- Images are stored per item per vendor: vendors[vi].images[itemIndex]
- Max image size before storing: warn user if file exceeds 1MB
- Always initialize images array when creating a new vendor or adding new items
- Strip images from Excel export — export text data only

## Excel export
- Always strip HTML tags from notes before writing to Excel
- Use fmt() for all numeric values written to cells
- Never export image binaries to Excel — skip images silently
- Always handle export errors with try/catch and show alert with error message

## Notes and rich text
- Empty note = "", "<br>", or "<div><br></div>" — treat all three as empty
- Always sanitize notes before saving to state
- Always strip HTML tags before writing to Excel
- Rich text editing uses contentEditable — never use textarea for notes

## Scoring logic
- Never rewrite or inline scoring calculations — always import from src/scoring.js
- calcTotal(), calcSec(), hasFail() are the only scoring functions — do not create alternatives
- Weight: 0 = Преимущество (excluded from score), 1 = Требование, 2 = Требование!
- Unfilled item (null) = 0 earned points but still counts toward maxPts

## Vendors
- Max vendors: 10 (matches VC color array length in constants.jsx)
- Vendor color: always VC[vendorIndex % VC.length]
- Never hardcode vendor colors inline — always use VC array

## UI behaviour
- List reordering: use ↑/↓ buttons with array swaps in state
- Never use native HTML5 drag-and-drop API
- Modals and popups: manage via state (null = closed, value = open)
- Confirm dialogs (reset, delete): use inline confirm UI, never window.confirm()

## Equipment types
- Only two valid eqType values: "стойка" and "pdu"
- Switching eqType reloads sections, vendors, techSpecs from their respective defaults or localStorage
- Always persist eqType to localStorage on change

## Print
- All print styles live in @media print block inside index.css
- Never add print-specific styles inline or in component files
- Buttons, nav, footer must be hidden in print: use [data-nav], [data-footer], data-no-print attributes

## Fonts
- Google Fonts Inter must include italic weights:
  ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;0,700;0,800;1,400;1,500;1,600;1,700;1,800

## Refactoring rules (active phase)
- We are incrementally extracting code from App.jsx — one concern at a time
- Each step must leave the app fully working before moving to the next
- Target: App.jsx ends up ~150 lines — routing, global state, top-level layout only
- Commit after every completed extraction step